- On climate change, Johnson said "We've got to be honest, the COP 26 summit here in Glasgow is not going to fix it in one go. We're not going to arrest climate change right here, right now. That is just impossible. And and I think everybody has got to be realistic about that."

- Last week, former MP Paterson was found to have broken lobbying rules and faced suspension from his post until Tory MPs blocked it and, instead, called for an "overhaul of the MPs' standards watchdog," BBC reports"}}]
